  BuildLang's parallel-iterator API surface - the ParallelIterator and
  IntoParallelIterator traits and the par_iter / map / filter / reduce / collect
  method names - is deliberately modeled on rayon's public API so the two are
  familiar to the same audience.

  The BuildLang implementation in buildlang/src/concurrent/parallel.bld is an
  independent reimplementation. It uses a batch Consumer and a hand-rolled
  split/join over BuildLang's own thread pool, and does not reproduce rayon's
  source or its internal architecture (it has no UnindexedConsumer, Producer,
  bridge, or Folder machinery; its trait contract is drive / Consumer::consume
  over a Vec, not rayon's drive_unindexed / Folder streaming model).

  rayon appears only as a transitive, development-only dependency of the Rust
  compiler crate, pulled in by the `criterion` benchmarking framework. It is not
  a runtime dependency of BuildLang and no rayon source is vendored.
